3.00	Marc_Pingris	Marc Pingris	Jean Marc Pingris, Jr. (born October 16, 1981) is a Filipino professional basketball player in the PBA for the B-Meg Llamados. He is a versatile 6-foot-5 forward-center who can post up, shoot mid-range jumpers, and block shots. He is half-French and half-Filipino. He is married to actress Danica Sotto, daughter of Vic Sotto, and has a son named Jean-Michel.	
